phase2.explanation:
🤖 **Sealed classes have specific rules for subclasses and when handling.**

**Problem 1: Object missing extension**
```kotlin
sealed class Result {
    data class Success(val data: String) : Result()  // ✅ Extends
    object Loading  // ❌ Missing : Result()
}
```

**Fix:**
```kotlin
object Loading : Result()  // ✅
```

**Problem 2: Subclass outside sealed class**
```kotlin
class CustomResult : Result()  // ❌ Only allowed in the same file
```

**Fix:**
```kotlin
// Put CustomResult inside the sealed class
sealed class Result {
    data class Custom(val data: String) : Result()
}
```

**Problem 3: Non-exhaustive when**
```kotlin
when (result) {
    is Result.Success -> { }
    is Result.Error -> { }
    // ❌ Missing Loading
}
```

**Fix:**
```kotlin
when (result) {
    is Result.Success -> { }
    is Result.Error -> { }
    is Result.Loading -> { }  // ✅
}
```

**Kotlin-chan says:**
"Sealed classes demand completeness. Use them right."

**Rules:**
1. All subclasses must extend in the same file
2. Objects must explicitly extend
3. When must be exhaustive
4. Subclasses cannot be created outside

